This page documents '''glitches, bugs, and exploits''' in '''[[Soul Blazer]]''' (SNES).

==Overview==
Soul Blazer contains several programming bugs and exploitable behaviors. Most are minor, but some can significantly affect gameplay or speedruns.

==Beneficial Glitches==

===Damage Boost Skip===
'''Discovered by:''' Speedrun community

By taking damage at specific locations, the knockback can push the player past obstacles or trigger warps early.

====How to Perform====
# Find a damage source near a barrier or wall
# Position so knockback direction is toward the obstacle
# Take damage at the right frame
# Invincibility frames allow passing through some collision

====Locations====
