===Magic Stacking===
'''Type:''' Effect duration bug

Casting certain magics rapidly can stack their effects, increasing damage or duration.

====Affected Magics====
* Rotator: Multiple orbs can exist simultaneously
* Flame Pillar: Damage ticks can overlap
* Soul Blade: Hit detection stacks briefly

====Execution====
# Cast magic
# Quickly open menu
# Use another magic item
# Effects may combine

==Harmful Glitches==

===Save Corruption===
'''Type:''' Memory corruption

Rare circumstances can corrupt save data, resulting in lost progress.

====Known Causes====
* Power loss during save
* Cartridge contact issues
* Dirty battery contacts

====Symptoms====
* Missing items
* Wrong area on load
* Corrupted player stats
* Checksum mismatch (detected by game)

====Prevention====
* Clean cartridge contacts regularly
* Avoid interrupting saves
* Make backup save states (emulator)

====Technical Details====
<pre>
Save checksum at $70:0004 (per slot)
If checksum fails, slot marked invalid
Checksum = Sum of bytes $0006-$07FF
</pre>

===Softlock - Leo's Painting===
'''Type:''' Progression blocker

If player enters Leo's painting without completing certain prior events, they may become stuck.

====Trigger Conditions====
* Enter painting before talking to Dr. Leo
* Enter painting without Spirit Sword
* Sequence break through wall glitch

====Escape Methods====
* Use warp magic (if available)
* Reset and reload save
* Some emulators: save state reload

===Softlock - Ghost Ship===
'''Type:''' Progression blocker

Ghost Ship has specific requirements that can leave player stranded.

====Requirements====
* Spirit Sword must be equipped
* Cannot switch weapons in certain areas
* Must clear all lairs in order

====Prevention====
* Always have Spirit Sword before entering
* Clear lower deck before upper deck

===Audio Glitch===
'''Type:''' Sound driver bug

Occasionally, audio may loop incorrectly or become distorted.

====Symptoms====
* Music stuck on single note
* Sound effects playing continuously
* Volume fluctuations

====Fix====
* Enter/exit area (forces music reload)
* Open and close menu
* Reset game (if persistent)

